cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.CE, cs.LO

This paper deals with the security of encryption schemes in the quantum world, which is a topic closely related to cryptography (cs.CR). It also involves the study of quantum information theory (cs.IT) and the design and analysis of quantum algorithms (cs.CC). The paper proposes a new definition of quantum indistinguishability and investigates its properties, which falls under the category of computational complexity theory (cs.CE) and logic in computer science (cs.LO).
